==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Remedial
<hw>Re*me"di*al</hw> <pr>(-<it>a</it>l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>remedialis</ets>.]</ety> <def>Affording a remedy; intended for a
remedy, or for the removal or abatement of an evil; <as>as,
<ex>remedial</ex> treatment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Statutes are declaratory or <qex>remedial</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is an evil not compensated by any beneficial result; it is not
<qex>remedial</qex>, not conservative.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Remedially</ent>⟦br⟧
